results.title: The Remarkable bandicoots
results.creator_credit: David Moore, Peter Du Cane, Film Centre (Perth, W.A.) and Wildfilm Australia
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Fauna”.
Until 1930 the Rabbit-Eared Bandicoot, or Bilby, was relatively common in various parts of Australia but suddenly it disappeared from many of them. Today it is the subject of an intensive search and study sponsored by the World Wildlife Fund. The program investigates the history and mystery of this beautiful marsupial. Narrated by David Moore.

results.title: The Tiny Carnivores
results.creator_credit: Peter Du Cane and David Moore
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Fauna”.
In this huge country most of the carnivorous mammals are tiny, and many are marsupials. Typically they are small but fierce predators of insects, spiders and grubs, but some - notably the native cats and Tasmanian Devil - are larger and more formidable. The program explores the behaviour of these animals.

results.title: The Silver Gull
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Fauna”.
This program shows that the Silver Gulls have a fascinating behaviour and ecology. As well as their interaction with humans, we see their beautiful off-shore island nesting grounds where thousands of birds compete for territory. Sharing this idyllic habitat with the gulls are Sea-Lions, with quaint antics on shore and graceful gymnastics in the water.

results.title: KKND: Krush Kill 'N Destroy for DOS
results.material_description: CD-ROM videogame. CD-ROM, CD jewel case with insert and manual in cardboard box
results.brief_description: In the far future of KKND: Krush Kill ‘N Destroy, a nuclear war has destroyed the Earth’s surface. The humans that were left split into two factions: The Survivors are the descendants of humans who managed to burrow under the Earth’s crust before the surface’s annihilation, taking with them what they could salvage. They survived underground for sixty years but dwindling resources has forced them to resurface. They were met by the Mutes, humans who lived through the nuclear destruction, mutated and dominated the Earth. An armed conflict between the two groups is inevitable. The game has you choosing either of these factions. As a classic real-time strategy, the focus on this game is gathering oil, building up and upgrading your base, training units and completing your objectives. Objectives can range from simply destroying an enemy presence to gathering a set amount of materials while fending off enemy attacks.

results.title: Diabetes
results.creator_credit: Milan Chvostek and Canadian Broadcasting Corporation
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “The Nature of things”.
Various researchers explain the nature of diabetes; it differs when it attacks children and adults.A mother and daughter comment on the effect the illness has on the latter and how through family and outside support she copes with it. An adult man discusses his illness and Dr. Best explains, with the help of old photographs, how he and Dr. Banting discovered insulin - which we see being manufactured.

results.title: The Moghul emperors
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Journey into India”.
The Moghuls, described by some historians as the most brilliant dynasty of emperors in modern times, ruled India from the 16th century to the middle of the 18th century. Keith Adam visits many of the monuments they created, including the Taj Mahal, and recreates their colourful history.
